
1) Installation on Fugaku side.
   ssh to login2(134.160.188.26)
   $ export TOP=/home/hp150019/data/share
   $ cd $TOP
   $ git clone https://github.com/yutaka-ishikawa/jit-dt.git
   $ cd jit-dt
   You will see the README-FUGAKU that is this file.
   $ cd src
   $ export INSTTOP=$TOP/nowcast
   $ make fugaku_client
   $ make install_fugaku_client
   $ mkdir results
   $ cd $INSTTOP/bin
   $ ./jit-fugaku-lwatch start
   See the daemon is correctly running.
     $ $INSTTOP/saitama/log
     $ cat LWATCHLOG.1
2) Installation on NICT side.
   ssh to DS01 via dp4 via ssh.nict.go.jp
   $ cd ~/tokyo/bin/
   edit the jit-dt-saitama-fugaku file and change the following variables
      REMOTEUSER
      REMOTEDIR
      PKCS11
   It is required a private key for the daemon process.

3) Test the watch_and_transfer command, invoked by
   the jit-dt-saitama-fugaku script, on NICT side.
   The following example is just for a transfer test without daemonize.
   You will see the transfer progress.
   Be sure that ssh agent is working
   $ printenv | grep SSH
   If the agent is working, you will see the SSH_CONNECTION varible.
   Then,
   $ export TOP_DIR=~/tokyo
   $ export REMOTEDIR=/home/hp150019/data/share-test/nowcast/saitama/
   $ export REMOTEUSER=u01148
   $ ~/tokyo/bin/watch_and_transfer \
	sftp:u01148@134.160.188.26:$REMOTEDIR/data/ \
        /mnt/latest-raw/ \
	-p 22 \
	-c $TOP_DIR/etc/serverconf \
	-n $TOP_DIR/jitready:$REMOTEDIR/bell// -v \
	-f $TOP_DIR/JITLOG \
	2021-0429/14/
   You will see transfer log messages every about 30 minutes.

4) Run a test program on Fugaku side
  $ cd $TOP/
  $ pjsub run-pltranstest2-fugaku.sh
  The script assumes that the jit-fugaku-lwatch runs on login2.
  If not, please change the first argument of the f-pltranstest2 program.

5) End of testing
   5.1) Stopping the watch_and_transfer command on NICT side.
   	To stop the command, just type control-C on the shell executing
	the watch_and_transfer command.
   5.2) Stopping the lwatcher command on Fugaku side.
	$ cd $INSTTOP/bin
	$ ./jit-fugaku-lwatch stop

6) Now run a demon on NICT side
   $ ./jit-dt-saitama-fugaku start
   Please look at the log file if the daemon is working.
